<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="437" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Burlingame</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-14"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 14, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 18th of June, No. 83,
                            enclosing a copy of your communication of the 15th of the same month to
                            the Consul General Seward, containing your construction of the rights
                            and duties of American citizens in China, directions in relation to
                            ships and passports, and general suggestions in reference to the
                            co-operative policy agreed upon by the representatives of the treaty
                            powers at Peking, has been received, and it is approved with much
                            commendation.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>